    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1911-07-08T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1911-07-08T00:00:00-05:00" n="109"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d109">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 611.3731/36.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Minister</gloss> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Habana</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1911-07-08">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 8, 1911</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 986.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to my dispatch No. 917, of the 9th
                    ultimo, and to previous correspondence in regard to the revision of the
                    reciprocity treaty between the United States and Cuba, and the imposition of a
                    tariff surcharge in certain cases, I have the honor to report that the bill in
                    question duly passed the Cuban Chamber of Representatives after the surcharge
                    provision had been stricken out. No action was taken on the bill by the senate,
                    however, and consequently it goes over until congress meets again in
                    November.</p>
                <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">John B. Jackson.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
